Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.22,0:00:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This month I’d like to talk\Nabout “Presenting Your Gifts to God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.99,0:00:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We certainly have every reason\Nto consider this topic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.76,0:00:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.76,0:00:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s because Jehovah gives us so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.13,0:00:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,James 1:17 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.77,0:00:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“Every good gift and every perfect present
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.24,0:00:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“is from above,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.27,0:00:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,coming down from the Father\Nof the celestial lights.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.21,0:00:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, Jehovah allows us\Nto enjoy the gift of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.65,0:00:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,even though our first parents
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.08,0:00:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,tried to take that from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.02,0:00:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s provided us with a variety of foods.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.72,0:00:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The environment\Nis just right to support life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.06,0:00:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s given us his precious Word, the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.23,0:00:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can come to know him\Nand his purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.57,0:00:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And the greatest “perfect present”\NJehovah has given us
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.21,0:00:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is the ransom.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.21,0:00:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah sacrificed a great deal
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.68,0:01:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to arrange for Jesus to buy back for us
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.35,0:01:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the hope of everlasting life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.18,0:01:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This was at no obligation on Jehovah’s part.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.75,0:01:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It was totally a gift of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.32,0:01:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Please read with me 1 John 4:9:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.43,0:01:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“By this the love of God\Nwas revealed in our case,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.53,0:01:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“that God sent his only-begotten Son\Ninto the world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.37,0:01:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we might gain life through him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.94,0:01:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What a gift of love from Jehovah, our God!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.81,0:01:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that move us to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.04,0:01:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you’ve had the experience\Nof a close friend or family member
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.05,0:01:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,unexpectedly giving you a valuable gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.42,0:01:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately, what are you thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.09,0:01:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You are probably trying to think\Nof what you can give in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.09,0:01:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How much more so would we want\Nto ‘present our gifts to God’
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.80,0:01:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to show our sincere appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.37,0:01:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,for all he’s done!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.54,0:02:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider some possible gifts
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.80,0:02:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah would be pleased\Nto receive from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.04,0:02:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of you in our viewing audience
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.08,0:02:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,have been moved to give your life to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.35,0:02:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,dedicating yourself to do his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.32,0:02:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s commendable!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.32,0:02:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what Romans 12 urges us to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.89,0:02:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there are some of you listening
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.13,0:02:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,who have thought about this way\Nof giving back to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.43,0:02:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but you haven’t yet taken this vital step.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.50,0:02:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice the appeal the apostle Paul makes
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.57,0:02:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,at Romans 12:1:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.60,0:02:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, I appeal to you\Nby the compassions of God, brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.51,0:02:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“to present your bodies\Nas a living sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.91,0:02:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“holy and acceptable to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.08,0:02:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a sacred service with your power of reason.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.38,0:02:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life is precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.79,0:02:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Presenting your body, your whole soul, to God
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.46,0:02:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of the best gifts you can give to him.
